name: TiffSaveOptions

properties.name: alphaChannels
properties.description: If true, the alpha channels are saved.

properties.name: layers
properties.description: If true, the layers are saved.

properties.name: annotations
properties.description: If true, the annotations are saved.

properties.name: spotColors
properties.description: If true, spot colors are saved.

properties.name: embedColorProfile
properties.description: If true, the color profile is embedded in the document.

properties.name: jpegQuality
properties.description: The quality of the produced image, which is inversely proportionate to the amount of JPEG compression. Valid only for JPEG compressed TIFF documents. Range: 0 to 12.

properties.name: byteOrder
properties.description: The order in which the bytes will be read. Default: Mac OS when running in Mac OS, and IBM PC when running in Windows.

properties.name: transparency
properties.description: If true, saves the transparency as an additional alpha channel when the file is opened in another application.

properties.name: layerCompression
properties.description: The method of compression to use when saving layers (as opposed to saving composite data). Valid only when 'layers' = true.
If true, the channels in the image are interleaved.
properties.name: interleaveChannels

description: Options for saving a document in TIFF format.
